The paper focuses on improving the channel model abstraction and studying the end-to-end performance of mmWave cellular networks, which are topics related to network infrastructure (NI) and information theory (IT). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of antenna arrays, which falls under multimedia (MM) and augmented reality (AR) categories. Finally, the paper evaluates the interplay between different elements in the protocol stack, which is related to systems and control (SY).
